<subSubSection id="C337088DF755B114B182FC7430C247E3" pageId="32" pageNumber="553" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8B925B06F755B114B182FC7432E4473C" blockId="32.[151,1437,799,1257]" pageId="32" pageNumber="553">
<collectionCode id="ED3CC3C3F755B114B182FC7432C240E0" box="[199,251,907,933]" pageId="32" pageNumber="553">TYPE</collectionCode>
MATERIAL: In his type description, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F755B114B3C9FC7431AA40E7" author="Sundevall, C. J." box="[652,915,906,933]" pageId="32" pageNumber="553" pagination="96 - 111" refId="ref29984" refString="Sundevall, C. J. (1850) Foglar fran sodra Afrika. Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps-akademiens forhandlingar, 7 (4), 96 - 111." type="journal article" year="1850">Sundevall (1850: 105)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned both males and females.According to his acquisition catalogue he actually had 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF755B114B3F2FC50315F408B" box="[695,870,943,969]" pageId="32" pageNumber="553" type="generic">four specimens</specimenCount>
at hand. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F755B114B28BFC5036D24088" author="Gyldenstolpe, N." box="[974,1259,943,970]" pageId="32" pageNumber="553" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref28755" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1926) Types of birds in the Royal Natural History Museum in Stockholm. Arkiv f or Zoologi, 19, 1 - 116." type="journal article" year="1926">Gyldenstolpe (1926: 62)</bibRefCitation>
refers to NRM 568759 [6848] as a “type”; we treat this as a 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F755B114B3DDFC2C313D40AF" box="[664,772,979,1005]" pageId="32" pageNumber="553">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation of this adult male collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F755B114B59BFC2C374640AF" box="[1246,1407,979,1005]" pageId="32" pageNumber="553" value="1840-04-19">
19 April 
<quantity id="4CD5F6E3F755B114B401FC2C374640AF" box="[1348,1407,979,1005]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6736" pageId="32" pageNumber="553" unit="in" value="1840.0">1840</quantity>
</date>
in Durban. The 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF755B114B077FC0830264753" box="[306,543,1015,1041]" pageId="32" pageNumber="553" type="generic" typeStatus="paralectotypes">three paralectotypes</specimenCount>
are: NRM 568758 [6850], a male collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F755B114B56AFC0836CE4753" box="[1071,1271,1015,1041]" pageId="32" pageNumber="553" value="1843-10-16">
16 October 
<quantity id="4CD5F6E3F755B114B5F9FC0836CE4753" box="[1212,1271,1015,1041]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.68122" pageId="32" pageNumber="553" unit="in" value="1843.0">1843</quantity>
</date>
in Saulspoort (Mohapoani); NRM 568757 [6851], a female collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F755B114B267FBE4363B4777" box="[802,1026,1051,1077]" pageId="32" pageNumber="553" value="1841-12-12">
12 December 
<quantity id="4CD5F6E3F755B114B282FBE4363B4777" box="[967,1026,1051,1077]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.67614" pageId="32" pageNumber="553" unit="in" value="1841.0">1841</quantity>
</date>
in Magalisberg; and a male [6849] collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F755B114B04CFBC033E9471B" box="[265,464,1087,1113]" pageId="32" pageNumber="553" value="1843-10-13">
13 October 
<quantity id="4CD5F6E3F755B114B0D0FBC033E9471B" box="[405,464,1087,1113]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.68122" pageId="32" pageNumber="553" unit="in" value="1843.0">1843</quantity>
</date>
in Saulspoort sent on exchange to 
<collectingRegion id="49E995E4F755B114B228FBC0318E471B" box="[877,951,1087,1113]" country="Germany" name="Berlin" pageId="32" pageNumber="553">Berlin</collectingRegion>
in 1853 (but not found in the ZMB database).
</paragraph>
